The American Stock Exchange said aninvestment trust which issues units in exchange for EastmanKodak Co &lt;EK> shares began trading today on a "when issued"basis.    AMEX said the trust, known as the Americus Trust for Kodakshares, trades under the ticker symbol KDUWI and will accept amaximum of 7,500,000 shares.    The trust included two categories which traded separatelyfrom the units, known as prime and score components, whichrespectively allowed investors to receive current income orcapital appreciation potential, it said. Reuter&#3;